e:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Universal Credit direct payments: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">more detail is needed in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">plans for a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">lternative payment arrangements and local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">support services. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">t is vital that local support services are effective and that suitable alternative paying arrangements are in place</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> order to prevent Universal Credit causing homelessness</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">7.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">St Mungo’s are implementing a strategy to boost the financial and budgeting skill</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s of our clients. However, uncertainty over DWP’s plans around alternative payments and local support services mean it is extremely challenging to plan how the support we provide can be coordinated with Universal Credit.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">7.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Universal Credit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ocal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">upport </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ervices </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ramework and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ternative payments arrangements guidance</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">set out the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment’s approach to deciding </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which claimants</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> should be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">exempt </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">from direct monthly payments and how budgeting support for claimants is to be provided. The current documents </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">set out an over</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">all approach but are lacking in detail</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">7.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The DWP’s direct payment pilots showed significant increases in rent arrears when dir</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ect payments were introduced.</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">irect payments have the potential to lead to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> increased levels of homelessness, substa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nce use and financial exploitation if the correct alternative payments and budgeting support are not in place.</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Alternative payment arrangement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and budgeting support must be targeted at the correct claimants and effectively administered.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> In this context r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eports </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">around </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">problems in administering the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">so far </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">extremely limited roll out </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Universal Credit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> are cause for deep concern.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">7.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There is a particular need for clarity over arrangements and support for claimants transitioning from supported to independent acc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ommodation. There is a risk that claimants could move from living in supported accommodation where there housing costs are paid directly to their landlord</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to living </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> independent accommodation with no support available</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and receiving all of their Univers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">al Credit award in one monthly payment.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">St Mungo’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">clients rely on the social fund to furnish accommodation when they move from our projects</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> into independent accommodation.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The transfer of responsibility for the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">much of the social f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">und to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> local authoritie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">s has seen varying </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">provision</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> put in place</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">. Two issues which have affected our clients are:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Local authorities have refused assistance to people </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">who are moving out</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">side</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">boundaries. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">This means people are treated as not resident anywhere for local sup</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">port fund purposes and so cannot access any funds</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">People in this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">situatio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> may </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">not be able to ask for help from the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local authority that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> they are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> moving into</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ey</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> are likely to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> need assistance before mov</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ome </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local authorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> require a minimum residence period before applications will be considered. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Good practice standards should be adopted across London – or preferably nationwide – so that no</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">one finds that they are effectively not treated as resident anywhere for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">loc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">al suppo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rt fund</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> purposes and so cannot access any funds.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Requirements to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> apply for a budgeting loan before a local support fund will be considered</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> have been put in place in some areas </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">result</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in homeless people starting a new tenancy saddled with debt,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> undermining their chances of sustaining the tenancy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The scheme operated by the DWP did not require a budgeting loan application to be applied for before a Commun</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ity Care Grant would be awarded. It is unclear why some local authorities have decided to ado</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pt this measure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, unless it is an attempt to deflect costs that they should meet onto the DWP.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The replacement of council tax benefit with localised schemes has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> led to significant extra costs for people</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> on low incomes, particularly in poorer areas</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">9.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">St </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Mungo’s works across a number of local authority areas, we have seen significant variation in the way in which local schemes to replace council tax benefit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> operate. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We have observed that p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eople on low incomes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">some of the poorer areas in which we operate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> have been asked to make the highest contribution to council tax. This can </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">means that people are now expected to pay a significant proportion of their income on council tax.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">9.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">St Mungo’s runs Peer Advice Link, a resettlement and tenancy support programme st</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">affed by volunteers. One of our volunteers now has to pay £13 a month in council tax. His income consists of £56.80 a week Jobseekers Allowance.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> He therefore has to spend over five per cent of his income on council tax.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">23 September 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-fam